{
  "message": "test(conformance): add EVAL test for nested table assignment write-back\n\nAdd fixture case 'eval_nested_table_assignment_writes_back' to the core\nscripting conformance suite. The test verifies that Lua nested table\nfield assignment (t.a.b = 42) correctly writes back through the table\nreference chain and returns the updated value via 'return t.a.b'.\n\nThis exercises the Lua VM's SETTABLE/GETTABLE opcode handling for\nmulti-level table access patterns, which is a common source of bugs\nin custom Lua implementations.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
